content: It's a good game but it gets boring when you never update it
What's the code for the locked door?
WHY DOES IT SAY LICENSE CHECK FAILED? I PAID FOR THIS GAME! WHAT THE @#&$? But... It is a good game and is way better than space agency 1 when it doesn't say LICENSE CHECK FAILED.
Every time I try to open the app I get the nooleus screen and then a black screen with music and that's it. I bet it's a fun game too
I love it. I have watched your progress in making this game through your social media anme a long way! Great job! And thanks for making a game like this!

Very good game. Just make 2d available, add new parts consistently, make orbit and planetary transfers more realistic, add ACTUAL real life rockets like in Space Agency 1, and not abandon this game like Space agency 1.
Great game but I need my money back to buy new things that I want
Good game but I can't control well
Amazing
This is the laziest, hardest to work with sequel ever. I used to have to work for orbit...now I just wait
How do i delete a failed save???

What happened guys first one was amazing the second one no I requested a refund you want to download this should probably do as well although admittedly the first one is well worth everything you put into it but not the second one
Its great
Love the new look, but a bit disappointed it changed so much from the original. Its more of a sim. Hopefully the campaign will change this. Can't recommend in its current form to fans of the first.
Very good game, one question, why do the doors lock when the game is not multiplayer
Hard to play wish I could refund it
Can't wait to see whats next for this game
1 star becouse i payed for the app ,installed it and the app give the error "app closed ,restart the app " so i payed for something that didnt work , please fix it or i want a refund
Thought we would get a more updated version of the fist but this was just a disappointment from top to bottom.

Great sequel to the original. Instructions could be more in depth. Sandbox type with no challenges (yet) and a limited size system. Already been everywhere. Real good start! Please expand!!! Please please!

I'm a bit disappointed. I was a big fan of the first game, and expected the same gameplay with improved graphics and content. This version of the game looks like it's only half finished. It has great opportunities, looks nice, but missing the missions, the campaign, the content. Now "only" a sandbox. Please don't stop here, continue the development with adding a real campaign.

This is such an AWESOME game. Once you get a hold of how things work your addicted. Would love to have an option to save your file on the cloud so if your hardware blows up you don't loose anything. Space Agency has that and saved my meon a couple of occasions. Minor update Things like the command module and the onboard computer, for noobs like me it would be nice to have a user's manual site to learn more on how things work. Cannot get any rocket link ups to the command module....HELP!
Good can you add the sea dragon

The app was working now suddenly, there app seems to be freezing immediately after the slash screen. Tried clearing cache, clearing data, uninstalling, and reinstalling. Same result. Did something happen in an update?

Tutorial really doesn't give me any clue to starting the game. The game is more like a sandbox and less of a career. No missions, no goal. No timewarp, enjoy waiting for minutes getting to planets. Also, you can make infinite money by selling all the material in first warehouse before razing and rebuilding it (building first warehouse is free and provides 4 initial resources). Nooleus, pls fix. P.S. game's fine, enjoyed my first 2 hours waiting my trip to Ico only to find out there's no uranium.

This game is a HUGE step up from the 2D version. I wish there was quests to do to make money or something of the sorts. The controls are challenging but aren't to different from the older version. Nice job!

Very little instructions. Tedious gameplay. Would have been better to have missions to help learn the game. Original game far superior - only lacked sprites of astronauts in the game. Don't waste your money!
Crashed upon opening. Unplayable. What a waste of my money and time.

Love the new 3d look . In space is a little dark for my liking . Would be nice if you could change the lighting . Not enough information on how to use the parts Tried to use the magnetic tug and couldn't get it to stop tumbling. Faults can be annoying would be nice to have a level where you could just build things and not have some alert coming up every 5 minutes . Would be nice to have the Saturn 5 and the Luna lander on it. Maby the Space shuttle also. All in all a very challenging game and addictive.
The text shows as black boxes and makes the game unplayable. I'm excited to play, but I cant until this bug is fixed.

I must say that this game has been fun for a while,I always have been looking for games that have complex gameplay and I never really find any on mobile,this is one of the best complex games you can possibly find out there for mobile,PS i think we need a guide to how to get the satellites to be charged,cuz I put one on the rocket, launched it,then I was trying to turn it on in space,no power it says,please make a guide for that:(

If you like Kerbal Space Program on PC then you gonna like this!!! Only thing I would change would be if I was the developer I would make EVERY attempt to make a multiplayer or at the very least a LAN network setting so your friends & family can play with you on the selfsame wifi network...constantly having to directly control the astronauts to water & resupply things like the Hydroponic Station/s get to be rather tedious & time consuming so having a extra set of hands would be awesome...

The long awaited sequel! I like the new 3D look but the graphics seem a little simplified. I personally liked the other one where you had all the historic rockets but I do enjoy the challenge of running bases. All and all it's a solid game.
Keeps crashing after splash screen
I'm sad, it doesn't work on my phone. Just keeps crashing at start up.

Space Agency 2138 is a pretty great game, I just don't really have time to play it. It is quite the upgrade from the original space agency, in both graphics and gameplay. The controls are okay, a little hard to use though. I would highly recommend this game, its a litttle like Kerbal Space Program, just for mobile devices. The price is also just right as well. Nooleus, great work on this game!
Disappointed!

I'm so glad it finally came! It does automate several processes (launch and reentry) taking control away from the user, but to be fair those stages can get monotonous when you do them alot, so I get, but if you like that part you may miss. Glad to have orbital maneuvering. It is simplified, you don't get to rendezvous or transfer, it's all about docking but it is fun. That best thing this game has that KSP doesn't: comprehensive resource management. Looking forward to that challenge.

Controls are a bit awkward. Especially moving around in interiors. The tutorials don't explain very much about the mechanics of the game. (They do explain the basics, but I have mostly been learning things through trial and error.) Yet I still overall have enjoyed it. Though it does take some getting used to. (Also, had a resupply module use it's thruster and fly backwards while on autopilot. Very confusing, and I don't think it was intentional)

Unexpected. Itll be great to see where you go from here. Love your other games. The concept here is good. There are a number of things that are very tedious on a phone. Like collecting resources. Takes a good while to manage things. But overall an impressive endeavor. Props to nooleus. Thanks for another great game.

This is a great game. Simple in most ways but open enough to have challenges such as being able to program the builder (thanks for the Easter egg). Love adding more parts to my station as the game develops. Air and water silos would be good to keep hydro and tubes supplied as would a medical bay to lower radiation. It would be nice if an astronaut left on planet could empty mines for you. Would be good if you could direct resources to specific warehouses on unload. Needs to save to Google play.

AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHHH!!!! I'M SO HAPPY!!!! I was in LOVE with space agency, I loved it so much. I was looking to install it again when I saw this and I am BLOWN AWAY!!! THEY HAVE EVERYTHING! IT'S LIKE KERBAL SPACE PROGRAM FOR ANDROID!!! I'M SO HAPPY!!! It was SO worth the 5 bucks. It was worth it and MORE! OOOOOHHHHH MY god I'm so happy. I would deadass pay 20 bucks for this. It's sooooo great. I love you, Nooleus!

Great game. Play the regular space agency and I'm happy with how the creator built both games. I rated the controls a 4 because there needs to be more options available rather than the one control setup that's preset. It works fine but moving around the buttons or being able to flip the turning ability so the direction you swipe is the way you turn instead of the opposite it's currently set at. I know it's a new game but this is just advice that hopefully will be considered.
Controls aren't the best but overall good game, also try Space Agency!
Every time I play, maybe 5 minutes its say Licence Check Faild , Plz Fix this game , remove the license verification. ASAP
Great game, maybe just add more modules and vehicle's
This is the Game we have been waiting for. Plus Astronauts!!! Very new feel with a little getting used to. If you played the first, this has the same feel with a 3d environment. Devs still updating.

The game has reverted back to an unplayable state, the previously patched black character text bug is back. Everything isn't all bad with this patch though, now the game doesn't crash because it fails to render text, infact it hasn't crashed at all since I updated. I appreciate all the hard work you have poured into making this game and I know that very soon it is going to be one of the best on the app store, I also hope someday you will acknowledge or reply to these dynamic reviews I do.
Great app
Great game for anyone experiencing control loss in space it is you're gyro just replace it from warehouse.
Please add real life rocket. Also I had unloading glitch where I can't unload the rocket but I had my empty warehouse. Its wired. Please help

This was a great updated version for the original SA. I'm honestly impressed with the complexity of the game. Bravo to the development team! The only criticism is that I wish there was a tutorial on data packs and how to use those.
Great app, but please add a confirmation message if someone wants to dispose something. I disposed some Air by accident and can't get it back. Sad. So please do my request and everyone will be happy!
Can you add free play mode you get to do anything without having to spend anything also you get base's on all planets
Great game! With a little imagination, the options are unlimited!
Really great! Much better than the old space agency but would be great to have a career mode with objectives and grants to complete them! All in all a great game!

I love this game but the pirate mechanic is a little annoying, and if you are reading this review and not know what I'm talking about its were you lose control of both your ship and astronaut(s) and i don't know how to gain control back sow dev if your reading this maybe you can tell this in the tutorial or make it to were you still control the astronaut(s) to go to a computer to stop the pirate.
Add were you can go out side space station

With the latest update this game is amazing! I love the level of detail as well as the functionality. With the latest update, I can finally launch more than one vessel into space at a planet and not have to constantly be hovering over it to ensure i don't lose an astronaut.
Great game but I'm just wondering can we travel to other planets ourselves and land on them

Big step up from the original game. Instead of maintaining everything about your space exploration, there are aspects that are done automatically such as re-entry. This game focuses more on base building and resource mining to keep your agency going. Cool aspect of the game is the ability to walk / float inside your space creations in first person view.

I like the game and its on its way to being incredible. Once a few control features are changed. Such as being able to double tap a neer by ship to control it instead of going through menus. And being able to hook up ship power, fuel, and air to one enother for easier transfers. Also i found the flight computer easter egg. Awesome suprise!

Great game. I wish it have the orbital maneuvers (station orbits planets..etc.) just like the first space agency game.Please add more crafts to build.. TIP: if you need money in game build Battery on your station and charge it, then you can transfer batteries in a container then fly back to earth and sell (you can get millions in just one full container of battery 😉

What a great game! I'm playing in hard mode and it took a couple tries to figure out how it works. Tip: Get a bunch of uranium mines going on Luna to keep the lights on and have regular resupply rockets moving the extra to Home. Solar panels fail a LOT and you'll drive yourself crazy and broke trying to keep them running.
Really cool, but please add an FOV slider and it kinda sucks that orbits aren't here yet
Extremely glitchy couldn't even get the app to open
Better than the first especially with the automated takeoff and re-entry.

Looks quite challenging! Love the look & the feel of everything! A total experience that's amazing in so many ways! Big thanks to Nooleus for getting it released! Can't wait to get 'ISAAC Organization' growing in the 22nd century! And why didn't somebody tell me about this two weeks ago??? 😆😆😆
Great 👍! Just a bit too much management before a launch but the game is awesome / Docking tutorial was painful / No bugs with my device.
Good
Upset that dont work on my android tv box but old one 2d work will this new 3d fail
Was a huge fan of the original, but in 3D this version is too difficult to orient and explore. Well programmed though, and decent graphics.

Major bug occurs when I finish a tutorial, or fire the engine of any craft. The game will crash, and will not start again unless I manually delete the user data, or uninstall the game (making it impossible to progress). Very dissapointing, I played a lot of the original Space Agency and was looking forward to playing this too. Hoping for a bug fix in future. Device is a Moto G5S

It's evident that a lot of work has gone into this game, but the change in focus makes it a completely different experience to the previous title. Building rockets is now a lot more laborious, while flying them is less interactive, and consequently less fun. The move to 3D doesn't really enhance the gameplay either, and the added realism isn't leveraged because of the limitations of mobile input. I loved the previous game, but this fell flat for me. I'm headed back to Space Flight Simulator.
The best space game I have ever played, thank you

Nooleus screen pops up when starting app, then either there is a dark screen with music playing, or earth shows up on the bottom of the screen and the app crashes. I use a Motorola G5 plus, maybe it's a graphic driver issue? Had fun playing the last game, I hope to play this one as well.
Love it! It surpassed my expectations and so far has no issues at all. By far the most fun space game on mobile. 10 out of 10!

I've been waiting so long for this. After playing it for hours, I'm already hooked, just like the first one. I hope to see more in future updates, but already this is awesome. I recommend this to anyone who played the first, or anyone who just... Wants to play a space themed game. Although I found a bug. One of my astronauts died while I wasn't watching the rocket, as it was going to re-enter. The game killed him, but I still got the Alert messages for him. And I could select him.
Awesome game and great support

A few bugs but I'm sure they will get fixed you can get around the keyboard bug with a wierd mouse Ive not had a great deal of time to play properly but the amount of depth for a phone game is amazing. And loving the lander style graphics The one thing I'd love to see is HID support
Unable to start game due to keyboard issue. Will update review once fixed.

I'm so happy!!!! Been waiting a while for this and it finally came out. Would be nice if there was a sandbox mode where you could do anything you wanted but I've been waiting far too long for this to complain.
Can't use keyboard so you can't start a new game. Needs to be fixed to be playable. Tutorial looked promising.
Works on my Motorola G8 Power Phone (Android Version 10) Will not start on my Samsung Galaxy A6 Tablet when I tap the app (Android Version 8.1.0)
Very fun!

Been waiting a while for this to come out. Been playing Space Agency like crazy lately. The graphics are awesome and the gameplay is really fun. Ive only just started so cant really comment on too much yet. My tablet doesnt support it which stinks but oh well ill deal with my phone screen. Im excited for future updates. Im hoping for some missions like in space agency and maybe the option to customize the game such as start with nothing but not have faults be frequent and such. Empty sandbox
Cant create new world
Brilliant! Theres a bug with the keyboard not popping up atm but you can get around this by using an app to bring it up externally. So much to do, this will keep me occupied during the lockdown!

Looks promising. I cant progress past the tutorials and start a new save because the text boxes wont bring up my keyboard so I can't enter a name for the save. I'm on a Samsung galaxy A8 if that's useful. Hopefully you can fix that soon. Thanks!
